: Combine the three drafted parts into a single, coherent, short operator-style note. Ensure the note flows well and accurately reflects the provided facts.\nComplexity: 4\nImportance: 9\nDependencies: step 1, step 2, step 3\nIndependent: no\nConfidence: high\nVerifiable: yes\n\n## Parent State\nThe task requires creating a short operator-style note in three parts, using only the facts provided in the prompt. The facts are:\n1. Open-Eywa treats the node as the durable unit of work.\n2. Mission runs are stored in mission folders.\n3. Testing improves reliability.\n\nThe plan decomposes this into drafting each of the three parts independently, and then a final synthesis step. This approach allows for focused work on each part before combining them, which aligns with the 'Analysis tasks' pattern. The plan is set to 'medium' review due to the need for careful phrasing in an 'operator-style' note.\n\nAlternatives considered:\n- A single step to write the entire note: Rejected because the prompt explicitly asks for decomposition into 'a few small writing steps' and then to 'complete them, then synthesize a final note'.\n- More granular decomposition (e.g., 'extract fact 1', 'write part 1'): Rejected as overly granular for this simple task. The current decomposition into drafting each part is sufficient.\n\nUncertainty:\n- The definition of 'operator-style note' is somewhat subjective, but the goal is to be concise and direct, as would be expected in an operational context.\n", "path": "input/context.md"}, "tool_name": "read_file"}, "role": "worker", "run_id": "run-001", "timestamp_utc": "2026-04-01T15:25:36.462186Z", "variant": null}
